Most specimens very light, appearing bi-coloured, lateral portions of the body dark, dorsal portion of head and abdomen lighter; hind femur without a longitudinal stripe (
Fig. 13A
), sometimes faint. Male paraprocts short. Female with subgenital plate broader than long (
Fig. 13C
), apices convergent; cercus rather constricted at base.

Colouration very dark; hind femur often uniformly dark. Male paraprocts very elongate (
Fig. 14C
), divergent; cercus minutely serrate on internal margin (
Figs 14I, J
). Female with cercus not constricted at base.
